tags.description: The Madam Brett Homestead is an early 18th-century home and grounds. Dating to 1709, it is the oldest standing building in its part of Dutchess County and has been listed in the National Register of Historic Places since 1976.
tags.name: Madam Brett Homestead

tags.description: Small public park, includes some flat open grass and a path through a wooded area with benches facing Fishkill Creek. Privately owned and managed by the Roundhouse but open to public; permits fishing. Hours dawn to dusk.
tags.name: Roundhouse Trail
